  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Beginning at 10th level, you can use your action to frighten someone with your menacing presence. When you do so, choose one creature that you can see within 30 feet of you. If the creature can see or hear you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier) or be frightened of you until the creature ends its turn out of line of sight or more than 60 feet away from you.</p>\n<p>If the creature succeeds on its saving throw, you can't use this feature on that creature again until you finish a long rest.</p>",
